  "country": "Japan",
  "notes": "This recording is also known under the name: \"Masada Five\".\r\nFor Asher Ginzberg (1856-1927), founding father of Cultural Zionism, who in the late 1880's, under the pen name of AHAD HA'AM (\"one of the people\"), passionately called out for a New Jewish Cultural Renaissance - one in which all Jews everywhere could find pride and meaning.\r\nRecorded at Power Station, NYC on July 16 & 17, 1995.\r\nMastered at Foothill Digital, NYC.\r\n\r\nⒸⓅ 1995 diskUnion\r\n",
